<br>
It's sort of an unfortunate thing in EverQuest and perhaps one of their biggest failures.  They failed to ever install a decent faction system regarding lore/characters.  Most people view religions as a punishment (except the Rallos Zek worshippers that get really nice cultural armor).  As it is, most of the religious flagged items suck, and there are no religious quests in the game.  You'd think my god would have something he'd want me to do.  *shrug*<br>
<br>
Of course, the storyline, when apparent, has always sucked in EQ.  That's why the game is predomenantly viewed as a game more like Doom than like a roleplaying one. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
